description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an ideal post for an existing Application Architect or an Experienced Software Developer with Application Design experience looking to step up into an Architect role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a design team who along with the Software Development team are developing the Health Board&#39;s digital platform in order to enable the Health Boards Digital Strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is challenging position with opportunities to learn and work with new technologies, including .Net Core, and HL7 FHIR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a PERMANENT position&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that applications should specifically addresses the requirements laid out in the attached Person Specification in order to considered for interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to know more about this role please contact me&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andy Warburton - Software Development and Enterprise Architect&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;andy.warburton@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07812679399&lt;/p&gt;
